.net%2FEldQ4%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Income%20of%20retirees%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22457%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20a%20quarter%20have%20incomes%20under%20%2410%2C000%2C%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emost%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eretirees%20have%20incomes%20under%20%2440%2C000.%20There's%20a%20dearth%20of%20middle-income%20retirees%2C%20with%20just%20about%2015%25%20raking%20incomes%20of%20%2450%2C000%20to%20%24100%2C000.%20But%20there%20seems%20to%20be%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20small%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewealthier%20concentration%20at%20the%20top%20of%20this%20group's%20income%20spectrum%2C%20with%20over%205%25%20of%20retirees%20making%20over%20%24100%2C000%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetirees'%20incomes%20come%20from%20various%20sources%3A%20Some%20still%20receive%20some%20type%20of%20wages%2C%20but%20many%20others%20get%20income%20from%20Social%20Security%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FVVC2x%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Retirees'%20sources%20of%20income%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22409%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F394943%2Fretiring-planning-retire-later.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPer%20Gallup%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20average%20retirement%20age%20in%20the%20US%20has%20been%20rising.%20In%201991%2C%20it%20was%2057%3B%20as%20of%202022%2C%20it%20was%2061.%20Similarly%2C%20Americans'%20%26quot%3Btarget%26quot%3B%20retirement%20age%20increased%20from%2060%20in%201995%20to%2066%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bfull%26quot%3B%20retirement%20age%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fbenefits%2Fretirement%2Fplanner%2Fagereduction.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%