india.com%2F309818%2Fiit-roorkee-startup-indi-energy-makes-sodium-ion-batteries-with-farm-waste%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eelectronic%20vehicles%20%3C%2Fa%3E(EV)%20market%20has%20already%20exploded%20in%20India%20in%20recent%20years.%20However%2C%20the%20notion%20of%20sustainability%20on%20account%20of%20the%20environmental%20impact%20of%20manufacturing%20batteries%20and%20the%20energy%20source%20to%20power%20these%20batteries%20is%20still%20doubtful.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20EVs%20and%20Renewable%20energy%20sources%20become%20more%20common%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20growing%20demand%20for%20energy%20storage.%20This%20means%20more%20batteries%20are%20needed%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20increased%20mining%20for%20materials.%20This%20puts%20further%20strain%20on%20the%20planet%20as%20we%20extract%20more%20resources%20for%20battery%20production%2C%E2%80%9D%20Akshay%20Jain%2C%20co-founder%20of%20Cancrie%2C%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20find%20an%20optimum%20solution%2C%20Akshay%20(36)%20along%20with%20his%20co-founder%20Mahi%20Singh%20(35)%20innovated%20nanocarbon%20for%20batteries%20from%20coconut%20shells.%20The%20patented%20technology%20is%20claimed%20to%20increase%20battery%20performance%20by%20125%20percent%2C%20thus%20reducing%20the%20need%20for%20raw%20material%20extraction%20for%20battery%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20using%20waste%20to%20make%20nanocarbons%2C%20and%20by%20adding%20it%20as%20a%20component%20into%20the%20existing%20batteries%2C%20we%20are%20increasing%20their%20efficiencies.%20This%20reduces%20the%20need%20for%20mining%20of%20rare%20earth%20metals%20and%20makes%20the%20planet%20more%20sustainable%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FCancr